#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:1
msgid "Zotero Citations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:3
msgid ""
"The [Zotero Citation module](https://omeka.org/s/modules/ZoteroCitation/)"
" allows users to access Zotero libraries to add citations using the "
"built-in rich-text editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:5
msgid ""
"Once activated, users set up their Zotero access from their user "
"settings. Their Zotero libraries will be accessible via HTML and other "
"blocks on [site pages](../sites/site_pages.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:7
msgid "Zotero Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:9
msgid ""
"The Zotero Citation module adds a number of configuration options to the "
"User Settings page. These are default settings for the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:11
msgid "Citation style: Select from a dropdown menu of available citation formats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:12
msgid ""
"Bibliography locale: Select a language locale for rendering the citation "
"and bibliography."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:13
msgid ""
"Bibliography link wrap: Check this option if you would like URLs for "
"bibliographies to wrap with the rest of the text of the entry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:14
msgid ""
"API library type: Select whether you would like to access a User library "
"or a Group library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:15
msgid "API library ID: Input the numerical id for the library you wish to access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:16
msgid ""
"API key: If you wish to access a library that is not public, you will "
"need to generate an API key from the Zotero account that owns the "
"library. Input that key here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/zoterocitation.md:17
msgid ""
"Search sort by: Select a sort field for search results when accessing "
"your library: Title, Creator, or Data Modified."
msgstr ""

